It's like everytime I read someone saying something stupid I look and there is Etnu's sig. <br>
<br>
Removeing the ley requirement to Vp would be silly and I doubt they will ever do it.  People worked long and hard to get keys for their entire guild and should be rewarded for the countless mindnumbing hours sitting in karnors basement etc.  If they revamp the zone well enough then people will go get new keys.  If they remove the key requirement then it will just be a newbie death trap.  God I can just see swarms of newbies asking for rotting loot.  Also Grimstaffs idea of the key only opening some parts of the zone...while I don't really like the idea it would be easily implementable as there are already mutliple large doors that require rouges to lockpick that could be made keyed only. <br>
<br>
IMHO how they should fix VP is this: first thing is the mobs on the 2 minute timer should stay. they make the zone fun and keep everyone awake.  I don't think they should mess with any of the mobs in the zone except to maybe give them all see invis.  As for the dragons? fix is quite simple, up their hp's into the 200-300k range maybe more.  Their Ae's are very nasty as it is and putting their hp's up into the 200k range would make them as difficult as any encounter in the game.  Personally I'd like to see the teleporting out requirement removed all it is is a nusaince as you can get ressed out anyway and it makes it difficult for people who have to leave for emergencies or just to sleep or whatever. It's A good idea but impossible to implement. <br>
<br>
As far as drops go, they should = tov drops, not any better not any worse. there are 7 dragons in this zone and Tov is getting crowded.  People will go there and clear the zone even if drops aren't any better than ToV.  <br>
