<br>
a.  revamp loot and make it heavy on the caster side with ok - great loot and a couple nice melee items.  New loot doesnt have to surpass or even rival NToV loot, but upgrades are needed badly.<br>
b.  leave it keyed, otherwise it's going to be nothing but newbie pickup raids getting slaughtered and /petitioning all day long.  Keyless is an invitation to CS nightmares.<br>
c.  put some TRIGGERED spawns in there for the rumored upcoming epic v2.o quests.  Give people a reason to go there, but for just one time, stop pitting guilds vs each other in a &quot;PvE&quot; game.  PvE is bullshit when you look at how VI deliberately pit's players against each other.<br>
d.  Change Trakanon and the key quest.  Give Trak regular dragon loots to replace the teeth and make the teeth come from a spawned Trak in the same temple that that the Emporer is in.<br>
<br>
Here's why<br>
- You can give mid sized guilds another Dragon encounter that &quot;uber&quot; guilds arent slaughtering 5 seconds after he spawns just for keys.  For mid sized guilds a Trak raid is AWESOME!  Why ruin it with a bunch of crappy key loots that they may never need.<br>
- Give the Emporer your 3 medalions and you receive a completed medallion.  Open up another room in the Temple and a mob or box that you give the medalion to spawns Trakanon's Guardian or something.  This mob drops ONE key half after being slain.  Make the turn in like a druids epic where you get the original part back.  So if you wipe, you can still summon Trak Guardian again, no loss of hours of camping.  Turn in Emporer medalion and TG loot for completed key.<br>
- Make the spawned Trak Guardian like some epics in that it's timed how often you can pull him up.  maybe every 2 hours like Naxot Deepwater for Clerics in Burning Woods.<br>
<br>
<br>
For anyone against the patching of the zone for the new Emporers area and spawned Trak Guardian... guess what, you dont have to do it unless you WANT to go to VP.  <br>
<br>
<br>
Anyway, thats the best way to improve the situtaion in my opinion.  Give mid sized guilds another encounter, give VP capable guilds a way of getting keys without interfering on a mob that others would enjoy, and make the reward not the BP from Trak but the loot thats inside the zone.  Verant could do all of that without changing the story line at all which is always one of their touchy points, staying with the storyline as they have it laid out already.  Also it's very minimal to add/change compared to the benefits. <p>Grumbles<BR>High Priest of The Kindred<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18964"> See my profile </a></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b> <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=101&stop=120>6</a><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=13037.topic&start=121&stop=121>7</a> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=13037.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=13037.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=13037.topic&index=40><img src=http://www.graffe.com/messageboard/add_reply.gif borde